# Commit Standards

## Conventional Commits Format
ALL commits MUST follow the format: `type(scope): description`

### Required Types
- `feat`: New features
- `fix`: Bug fixes
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `test`: Adding or updating tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

### Required Scope
- `readme`: README file changes
- `api`: API changes
- `helpers`: Helper function changes
- `logger`: Logger changes
- `storage`: Storage related changes
- `build`: Build system changes
- `deps`: Dependency changes

### Examples
- `docs(readme): improve README with comprehensive examples`
- `feat(api): add new HTTP client method`
- `fix(helpers): resolve date parsing issue`
- `chore(deps): update dependencies`

## NEVER commit without proper scope and type!